name: Ms Red.
description:
This is my first ever consistent-character textual inversion, I followed the handy guide produced by BelieveDiffusion, creator of the LastName series. you can find the guide HERE

For similar consistent-character embeddings by other authors check out znobody, nobody and noexist too.

For most of the example images I've used Deliberate v2. I ran this against 9 different checkpoints and the results ain't too shabby, try it! testing results below.

Instructions: Place the .pt file under stable diffusion/embeddings and then use the prompt msred_deliberatev2 - the embedding is named as such because that is the checkpoint I trained it on, but it works for other checkpoints as shown above.

Note: I could have just included all perfect images in the examples, but that's not representative. I've included some not-so-good-outputs for completeness, some are blurry/lacking fidelity because I'm still working on my upscaling process (please post tips if you have any! much appreciated)

Oh, and beware the spiderhands and ten-toes. 😉

These were all trained and generated on a 12gb RTX 3060, results were speedy and flawless for a fairly budget GPU 👍

Checkpoints tested against:

  • SD 1.5

  • Realistic Vision v2.0

  • HARDblend-NSFW

  • GalaxyTimeMachine's GTM "ForYou-Fantasy" v1.1

  • Deliberate v2

  • Clarity 2

  • Avalon TruVision v3.1

  • AnalogMadness v4.0

Credit to the authors of the above for some smashing models.

If I do any more of these I will tag them under dtmiss

Disclaimer: this is a fictional character and a experiment, any resemblance to actual persons is entirely coincidental.
